1.00	Canadian_Council_for_Israel_and_Jewish_Advocacy	Centre for Israel and Jewish Affairs	The Centre for Israel and Jewish Affairs (CIJA) (formerly the Canadian Council for Israel and Jewish Advocacy) was founded in 2004 as the principal advocacy, oversight and co-ordinating body for a number of Jewish Canadian organizations including the Canada-Israel Committee (and the Quebec-Israel Committee), the Canadian Jewish Congress/United Jewish Appeal and National Jewish Campus Life. It is the advocacy arm of the United Israel Appeal in Canada. Due to a restructuring effective July 1, 2011, these subsidiary organizations were dissolved with CIJA assuming their functions and responsibilities.	
